How to make perfect Besan Ladu Recipe | Halwai Style 1 kilo besan ladu recipe 

How to make Besan Laddu Flour -
 • Dry roast chana dal on very flame until they get light marks on it
 • Once done, allow the dal to comes at room temp & then take it to the flour mill for grinding
 • Make little coarse texture flour, which is perfect for laddus

How to make Besan laddu -
 • heat up some ghee into a kadhai, add besan & roast on low flame for 2-3 mins
 • then add some more besan & roast for 2 more mins, again add remaining besan & roast the besan on low flame until besan changes the color to light golden brown & get aromatic
 • While roasting the besan make sure to keep the flame low, roast continuously & break all the lumps from the besan
 • After 25 mins of roasting, if you find the besan is still dry then add some extra ghee
 • Once besan is roasted completely, sprinkle some water or milk & mix well for 2 mins & turn off the flame
 • Take the roasted besan to a parat or large plate & allow it to cool down
 • Once the roasted besan comes at room temp, add powder sugar & cardamom pw to it 
 • mix everything well, break sugar lumps if any & roll the laddus
 • Our delicious besan laddu is ready
